if we want to send http request using javascript, we need to use the XMLHttpRequest object
it's a default object available on js 

example :
const xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();

then we configure the request using the open() method
the method itself require 2 arguments 
1st argument is the type of request we want to send 
2nd argument is the url we targeted to

example:
xhr.open('GET', 'https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts');